29#include <libelf.h>

31#include "_libelf.h"

33__RCSID("$NetBSD: libelf_data.c,v 1.3 2016/02/20 02:43:42 christos Exp $");
34ELFTC_VCSID("Id: libelf_data.c 3174 2015-03-27 17:13:41Z emaste ");
35
36int
37_libelf_xlate_shtype(uint32_t sht)
38{
39 /*
40 * Look for known section types.
41 */
42 switch (sht) {
43 case SHT_DYNAMIC:
44 return (ELF_T_DYN);
45 case SHT_DYNSYM:
46 return (ELF_T_SYM);
47 case SHT_FINI_ARRAY:
48 return (ELF_T_ADDR);
49 case SHT_GNU_HASH:
50 return (ELF_T_GNUHASH);
51 case SHT_GNU_LIBLIST:
52 return (ELF_T_WORD);
53 case SHT_GROUP:
54 return (ELF_T_WORD);
55 case SHT_HASH:
56 return (ELF_T_WORD);
57 case SHT_INIT_ARRAY:
58 return (ELF_T_ADDR);
59 case SHT_NOBITS:
60 return (ELF_T_BYTE);
61 case SHT_NOTE:
62 return (ELF_T_NOTE);
63 case SHT_PREINIT_ARRAY:
64 return (ELF_T_ADDR);
65 case SHT_PROGBITS:
66 return (ELF_T_BYTE);
67 case SHT_REL:
68 return (ELF_T_REL);
69 case SHT_RELA:
70 return (ELF_T_RELA);
71 case SHT_STRTAB:
72 return (ELF_T_BYTE);
73 case SHT_SYMTAB:
74 return (ELF_T_SYM);
75 case SHT_SYMTAB_SHNDX:
76 return (ELF_T_WORD);
77 case SHT_SUNW_dof:
78 return (ELF_T_BYTE);
79 case SHT_SUNW_move:
80 return (ELF_T_MOVE);
81 case SHT_SUNW_syminfo:
82 return (ELF_T_SYMINFO);
83 case SHT_SUNW_verdef: /* == SHT_GNU_verdef */
84 return (ELF_T_VDEF);
85 case SHT_SUNW_verneed: /* == SHT_GNU_verneed */
86 return (ELF_T_VNEED);
87 case SHT_SUNW_versym: /* == SHT_GNU_versym */
88 return (ELF_T_HALF);
89 default:
90 /*
91 * Values in the range [SHT_LOOS..SHT_HIUSER] (i.e.,
92 * OS, processor and user-defined section types) are
93 * legal, but since we do not know anything more about
94 * their semantics, we return a type of ELF_T_BYTE.
95 */
96 if (sht >= SHT_LOOS && sht <= SHT_HIUSER)
97 return (ELF_T_BYTE);
98
99 /*
100 * Other values are unsupported.
101 */
102 return (-1);
103 }
104}
